    {
        "sha": "f2a24cfd80edfb6b04eb0de8bb5e233f132a176d",
        "author": "Jonathan Brossard",
        "email": "endrazine@gmail.com",
        "date": "2026-04-25T10:04:14Z",
        "message": "Apply Debian packaging patches (issue #51)\n\n- Fix doxygen LaTeX compilation bug (\\+ command)\n- Fix spelling errors in wcc.c, wld.1, wsh.c, wsh_help.h\n- Add shebang to main.wsh\n- Add non-Linux kernel support via local elf-em.h\n- Link libbfd statically (fixes Debian bug #949601)\n- Remove build timestamps for reproducible builds\n- Add CPPFLAGS/LDFLAGS support for Debian hardening\n- Remove accidentally committed Lua build artifacts\n- Improve .gitignore to exclude build artifacts\n\nPatches by Philippe Thierry and Debian Security Tools team\n<team+pkg-security@tracker.debian.org>\nReported in: https://github.com/endrazine/wcc/issues/51",
        "url": "https://github.com/endrazine/wcc/commit/f2a24cfd80edfb6b04eb0de8bb5e233f132a176d"
    },
    {
        "sha": "d5b1095f002b41bbb835e5db0d63cf776732871e",
        "author": "Jonathan Brossard",
        "email": "endrazine@gmail.com",
        "date": "2026-04-25T09:39:14Z",
        "message": "Vendor Lua 5.3.6 (replaces 5.3.0/1; fixes CVE-2020-24370 natively)\n\nPrevious vendored snapshot was Lua 5.3.0 or 5.3.1 (copyright 2015).\nLua 5.3.6 includes all 5.3.x bug fixes including the backport of\nCVE-2020-24370 (negation overflow in ldebug.c findvararg).\n\nCloses: PR #43",
        "url": "https://github.com/endrazine/wcc/commit/d5b1095f002b41bbb835e5db0d63cf776732871e"
    },
